{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584336"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:43:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:43:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14449"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14449"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.41,0.02,0.05,0.39,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7144"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55789"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7144"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14449"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41334"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4899"},{"type":"tags","id":"4900"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"8426"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17051"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17113"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55789"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is studying the internal anatomy of the heart during a dissection practical.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements is correct regarding the anatomy of the heart?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The left ventricle has more papillary muscles than the right ventricle","The outflow tract of the right ventricle is the aorta","The papillary muscles of the right ventricle are thicker than those of the left ventricle","The septomarginal trabecula is present in the right ventricle","The chordae tendineae attach directly to the ventricular walls"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe septomarginal trabecula is present in the right ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E. This structure, also known as the moderator band, is a distinctive feature of the right ventricle. It is a muscular band that connects the interventricular septum to the anterior papillary muscle, carrying a portion of the right bundle branch of the conduction system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E  \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe left ventricle has more papillary muscles than the right ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. The right ventricle typically has more papillary muscles (usually three) compared to the left ventricle (usually two).\u003C/li\u003E  \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe outflow tract of the right ventricle is the aorta\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. The outflow tract of the right ventricle is the pulmonary trunk, which carries deoxygenated blood to the lungs. The aorta is the outflow tract of the left ventricle.\u003C/li\u003E  \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe papillary muscles of the right ventricle are thicker than those of the left ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. The papillary muscles of the left ventricle are typically thicker and more robust than those of the right ventricle, corresponding to the higher pressures in the left ventricle.\u003C/li\u003E  \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe chordae tendineae attach directly to the ventricular walls\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. The chordae tendineae, also known as tendinous cords, attach to the papillary muscles, not directly to the ventricular walls. They connect the papillary muscles to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves (tricuspid and mitral valves).\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The septomarginal trabecula (moderator band) is a distinctive feature of the right ventricle."],"references":["Netter, F. H. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: Classic Regional Approach-Ebook. 2022. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sanz J, S\u00e1nchez-Quintana D, Bossone E, Bogaard HJ, Naeije R. Anatomy, Function, and Dysfunction of the Right Ventricle: JACC State-of-the-Art Review. J Am Coll Cardiol. 2019 Apr 2;73(12):1463-1482. doi: 10.1016/j.jacc.2018.12.076. PMID: 30922478.","Crucean A, Spicer DE, Tretter JT, Mohun TJ, Anderson RH. Revisiting the anatomy of the right ventricle in the light of knowledge of its development. J Anat. 2024 Feb;244(2):297-311. doi: 10.1111/joa.13960. Epub 2023 Oct 9. PMID: 37814425; PMCID: PMC10780169."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41334"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14449"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/41334"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-17T21:26:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T21:27:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7144"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55789"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"41","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/41"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc80","name":"Anatomy","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null